The paper discusses security and privacy issues in Smart Home Personal Assistants (SPA), which involves the use of AI and complex architectures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the interaction between users and SPA devices, which suggests a possible category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the use of AI in SPA suggests a possible category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of a wide range of underlying technologies, which suggests a possible category of cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses privacy issues, which suggests a possible category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
